The paper discusses modeling events in software engineering, which is a topic that falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of graphic languages in software development also suggests a possible connection to software design (cs.SD). The paper also mentions the input-process-output framework, which is a common concept in programming languages (cs.PL). The analysis of event processes and their mapping to generic processes could also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
